      "description": "Built for someone who knows what they\u2019re looking at, this car is a solid project with a drivetrain that still shows promising character and a chassis with plenty of life left for the next owner. It presents as a driver-grade fixer with visible wear, but it has the kind of honest, usable foundation enthusiasts appreciate: straightforward mechanical layout, good parts availability, and strong upside for someone wanting an affordable entry point. Ideal as a budget commuter project, weekend wrenching candidate, or donor for a larger build. Priced to move and worth a look for anyone who values mechanical potential over cosmetics.",
